 The customer is not available at the moment. 

86
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:24,860
The chairwoman is taking it too far.

87
00:08:25,660 --> 00:08:27,680
Did the director get fired?

88
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,050
All of a sudden?

89
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,400
Is this about the rumor involving Team Leader?

90
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,740
It can't be.

91
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:34,700
There's no other way to explain it.

92
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:37,070
And overnight? In the middle of the project?

93
00:08:37,070 --> 00:08:39,970
But still. Dismissal?

94
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:44,700
- What about our project? 
 - Team Leader.

95
00:08:49,850 --> 00:08:52,120
Director...

96
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:57,420
Team Leader!

97
00:09:00,930 --> 00:09:02,190
 The call is not going through. 

98
00:09:02,190 --> 00:09:04,670
 You'll be connected to... 

99
00:09:07,260 --> 00:09:08,590
Chief,

100
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:11,030
what happened to the director out of the blue?

101
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:12,580
You're in such a hurry.

102
00:09:12,580 --> 00:09:16,430
You aren't hiding your relationship anymore.

103
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:17,680
It's okay.

104
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:20,920
The chairwoman also knows about it now.

105
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,710
- Pardon? 
 - She knows when you

106
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:25,510
entered and left the director's house.

107
00:09:25,510 --> 00:09:26,810
She knows everything.

108
00:09:26,810 --> 00:09:30,030
Looks like she had many lookouts.

109
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:32,020
That's what happened...

110
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,400
Chief Kwon.

111
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:39,970
I quit.

112
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:44,040
- Why? 
 - Because I knew from the beginning.

113
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:47,140
But I kept it a secret.

114
00:09:55,050 --> 00:09:58,250
Take good care of the director.

115
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:01,250
But I'm relieved someone like you

116
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:03,400
is by his side.

117
00:10:18,230 --> 00:10:20,660
   

118
00:10:24,780 --> 00:10:28,630
Chief, where's the chairwoman right now?

119
00:10:51,930 --> 00:10:53,690
Chairwoman.

120
00:10:57,090 --> 00:10:58,950
How dare you come in here?

121
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:01,680
I know you aren't happy...

122
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,180
about our relationship.

123
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:04,770
But I won't let my

124
00:11:04,770 --> 00:11:06,970
personal feelings jeopardize Yongsung, so—

125
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:11,070
I said it'd be over if you disappointed me.

126
00:11:17,580 --> 00:11:19,420
Grandmother.

127
00:11:29,530 --> 00:11:31,970
You know I've done...

128
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:36,500
everything for Yongsung.

129
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,200
I'll be better from now on.

130
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:41,460
I'll work harder as your grandson.

131
00:11:41,460 --> 00:11:44,340
I thought you could be a substitute,

132
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:47,050
but you were a defect.

133
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:52,180
I'm disgusted that you're related to me.

134
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:54,560
What about me, then?

135
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:57,890
- What? 
 - Ever since my parents passed,

136
00:11:57,890 --> 00:12:00,750
I couldn't even be sad or happy freely.

137
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:02,850
Because I was always an unworthy grandson.

138
00:12:02,850 --> 00:12:04,950
No matter how painful that was,

139
00:12:04,950 --> 00:12:07,800
I endured it and worked hard every day.

140
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:10,450
I thought you'd acknowledge me someday

141
00:12:10,450 --> 00:12:12,560
if I lived the way you wanted me to.

142
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:16,420
I've been trying to satisfy your standards.

143
00:12:16,420 --> 00:12:19,220
But I can't even...

144
00:12:21,230 --> 00:12:23,670
- love her? 
 - Of course not.

145
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:25,860
You said you want to be my successor.

146
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:27,450
Love?

147
00:12:27,450 --> 00:12:29,170
With a junior employee,

148
00:12:29,170 --> 00:12:32,090
a daughter of a hardware store owner?

149
00:12:32,930 --> 00:12:36,300
I never should've accepted

150
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:39,010
someone who wasn't qualified.

151
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:43,630
I guess...

152
00:12:46,230 --> 00:12:49,630
I never would've been good enough for you.

153
00:12:49,630 --> 00:12:51,360
That's right.

154
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:06,630
 ­  

155
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:40,610
 I... 

156
00:13:40,610 --> 00:13:42,650
 will fill in for my father. 

157
00:13:42,650 --> 00:13:45,090
 I thought you could be a substitute, 

158
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:47,900
 but you were a defect. 

159
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:52,200
 I'm disgusted that you're related to me. 

160
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:31,670
 Are you okay? 

161
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:34,280
 Call me when you see this. 

162
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:42,870
 I'm okay. 

163
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:45,370
 I'm sorry for making you worry. 

164
00:14:47,930 --> 00:14:50,310
 See you after work. 

165
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:55,920
 Where are you? 

166
00:14:55,920 --> 00:14:58,370
 I'm leaving now. 

167
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:08,810
Here you are.

168
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:10,460
You must be hungry.

169
00:15:10,460 --> 00:15:11,800
What should we eat?

170
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:12,950
Director,

171
00:15:12,950 --> 00:15:15,780
you can tell the chairwoman that we broke up.

172
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:17,110
I really don't care.

173
00:15:17,110 --> 00:15:18,960
There's no need to deny our relationship.

174
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:21,240
And we shouldn't.

175
00:15:22,210 --> 00:15:24,380
I'm sorry for everything.

176
00:15:29,380 --> 00:15:30,800
Where should we go?

177
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:33,740
I can have a date anywhere now.

178
00:15:34,510 --> 00:15:36,010
You're right.

179
00:15:36,010 --> 00:15:38,230
We can do that now.

180
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:41,520
We can hold hands like this, too.

181
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:45,780
I like it.

182
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,970
You can go to concerts freely, too.

183
00:15:51,970 --> 00:15:53,700
Ever since I became public,

184
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:56,070
I never thought I'd go to a concert again.

185
00:15:56,070 --> 00:15:59,350
I can go to the next one now.

186
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:02,930
Should we go together?

187
00:16:02,930 --> 00:16:05,160
I'd love to go with you, of course.

188
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:07,360
I'll do the things you've done alone

189
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:11,030
with you from now on. Whatever it is.

190
00:16:11,030 --> 00:16:13,060
Sounds good.

191
00:16:13,060 --> 00:16:16,130
I'll be okay as long as I have you.

192
00:16:16,130 --> 00:16:18,630
You'll continue to be okay, then.

193
00:16:18,630 --> 00:16:21,900
Because I'll stay by your side.

194
00:16:28,810 --> 00:16:31,420
How could I not worry?

195
00:16:32,310 --> 00:16:34,780
 I'm with Su Jeong. 

196
00:16:36,850 --> 00:16:39,070
Kim Shin Won.

197
00:16:39,070 --> 00:16:41,690
Why is it so hard to see you these days?

198
00:16:41,690 --> 00:16:43,720
Because I've been with my girlfriend.

199
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,370
You think I don't know that?

200
00:16:45,370 --> 00:16:47,840
It's because you come home less these days.

201
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,990
Son.

202
00:16:49,990 --> 00:16:52,130
You said you don't do portraits.

203
00:16:52,130 --> 00:16:53,930
But look what you're working on now.

204
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:56,260
I wanted to draw it once.

205
00:16:56,260 --> 00:16:58,170
It'd be a nice gift later, too.

206
00:16:58,170 --> 00:17:02,470
Looks like you finally found the right one.

207
00:17:03,420 --> 00:17:05,770
I think so, too.

208
00:17:06,490 --> 00:17:08,570
Are you thinking of even marrying her?

209
00:17:08,570 --> 00:17:10,940
I haven't considered that yet, but...

210
00:17:10,940 --> 00:17:12,840
How should I say it?

211
00:17:12,840 --> 00:17:14,650
I want to always be with her.

212
00:17:14,650 --> 00:17:16,890
I don't want to be apart from her.

213
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:20,580
If I got to share a lifetime with her like you two,

214
00:17:20,580 --> 00:17:23,260
I'd definitely be happy.

215
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:31,840
I didn't think I'd be seeing you dressed like this.

216
00:17:32,530 --> 00:17:35,140
I'm no longer your boss.

217
00:17:35,940 --> 00:17:38,100
Why did you do that?

218
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:42,330
The fact that you upset the chairwoman.

219
00:17:42,330 --> 00:17:44,230
I just don't understand it.

220
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,400
Do you know...

221
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,300
when I started to respect and look up to

222
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:51,700
the chairwoman?

223
00:17:52,660 --> 00:17:57,150
This might sound cruel to you,

224
00:17:57,150 --> 00:17:59,360
but it was after she lost her son.

225
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:02,300
Seeing how strong she was at the time,

226
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:09,600
I thought, "I can trust someone like her."

227
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:15,730
You don't like espresso, right?

228
00:18:16,390 --> 00:18:20,200
You go to concerts sometimes.

229
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:22,630
I didn't check inside the packages

230
00:18:22,630 --> 00:18:25,590
you ordered under a strange name.

231
00:18:25,590 --> 00:18:28,030
When you knew all that,

232
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,640
why didn't you report it to her?

233
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:34,770
You hid that to become the person she wanted.

234
00:18:34,770 --> 00:18:37,880
Hiding emotions and suppressing them

235
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:41,940
couldn't have been easy, but you endured it.

236
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:46,810
That side of you resembled the chairwoman a lot.

237
00:18:46,810 --> 00:18:51,700
And I thought that was the successor she had in mind.

238
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:54,670
- Then, this time also— 
 - No.

239
00:18:54,670 --> 00:18:59,880
I was just an ordinary person, drawn to affection.

240
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,520
Being a successor is nice,

241
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:06,420
but I've known you since you were a child.

242
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:10,140
I thought it'd be nice for you to be happy

243
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:12,460
with someone you love.

244
00:19:18,330 --> 00:19:21,090
So, Chief Kwon...

245
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:22,990
that's how you felt.

246
00:19:23,660 --> 00:19:26,770
Yes. I did.

247
00:19:35,330 --> 00:19:39,930
Thank you for working with me all this time.

248
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,210
What do I do now?

249
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:11,470
 What are you going to do now? 

250
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:15,540
 Do you want to read comic books in the attic? 

251
00:20:15,540 --> 00:20:18,120
 I think Su Bin is home. 

252
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:19,940
 Okay. 

253
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,290
I'm nearing the shop now.

254
00:20:36,290 --> 00:20:39,030
Huh? I'm still on my way from grocery shopping.

255
00:20:39,030 --> 00:20:40,770
 It's okay. I can wait. 

256
00:20:40,770 --> 00:20:42,350
I took a half day off today.

257
00:20:42,350 --> 00:20:44,150
We really have to see a movie today.

258
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:47,260
We can't suddenly go to a hotel like last time.

259
00:20:47,260 --> 00:20:50,510
Didn't you gladly change the destination?

260
00:20:50,510 --> 00:20:54,770
Geez. We're on the same page too often.

261
00:20:54,770 --> 00:20:57,060
Okay, see you later.

262
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:24,950
What?

263
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:28,200
What are you doing here at this hour?

264
00:21:33,010 --> 00:21:35,380
So, your grandma threw you out

265
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:37,140
and you lost your job.

266
00:21:37,140 --> 00:21:39,690
That means you're...

267
00:21:39,690 --> 00:21:43,080
jobless. Just like me.

268
00:21:44,310 --> 00:21:45,430
Jobless?

269
00:21:45,430 --> 00:21:47,850
Well, aren't you?

270
00:21:47,850 --> 00:21:50,500
Do you have something to do?

271
00:21:51,370 --> 00:21:53,670
I do not.

272
00:21:53,670 --> 00:21:56,950
That's why you wanted to wait for Noona at our place.

273
00:21:56,950 --> 00:21:58,440
It's not exactly that—

274
00:21:58,440 --> 00:22:03,800
By the way, what exactly do you like about her?

275
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:05,130
She's pretty.

276
00:22:05,130 --> 00:22:07,340
Are you crazy by chance?

277
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:09,170
Being crazy in love isn't a sin.

278
00:22:09,170 --> 00:22:11,820
Geez, stop.

279
00:22:12,770 --> 00:22:16,240
I think I'll puke. Stop talking, please.

280
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:20,050
And she loves me as I am.

281
00:22:20,890 --> 00:22:23,430
She cried about breaking up.

282
00:22:23,430 --> 00:22:26,850
But you're both totally head over heels. Seriously.

