00:22:26,850 --> 00:22:29,650
Did Su Jeong cry?

284
00:22:29,650 --> 00:22:30,980
Yes.

285
00:22:30,980 --> 00:22:33,470
Dad and I never saw her bawling like that.

286
00:22:33,470 --> 00:22:36,400
It gave me chills... not.

287
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:38,420
Thinking now, she did that back then, too.

288
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:41,270
Because of Black Dragon or whatever.

289
00:22:41,270 --> 00:22:42,380
Black Dragon.

290
00:22:42,380 --> 00:22:44,730
There's this guy. He was her first love.

291
00:22:44,730 --> 00:22:47,040
Her dark days. If she finds out that I know,

292
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:49,310
she'd bite her tongue and kill herself.

293
00:22:49,310 --> 00:22:52,460
Did she cry a lot then, too?

294
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:53,750
Yes.

295
00:22:53,750 --> 00:22:55,800
She didn't eat for days.

296
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,820
Dad was very worried, too. But he couldn't show it.

297
00:22:58,820 --> 00:23:01,600
It was the most unfilial thing she did.

298
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:04,720
Eat.

299
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,450
Okay.

300
00:23:12,490 --> 00:23:15,010
   

301
00:23:15,010 --> 00:23:16,700
Father.

302
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:18,800
Hand me the heavy stuff.

303
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:21,030
What brings you here?

304
00:23:21,030 --> 00:23:24,140
I don't know. He suddenly wants to help you.

305
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:25,590
He must be busy, though.

306
00:23:25,590 --> 00:23:27,840
He's not. He's jobless.

307
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:29,390
I'll do my best to help you.

308
00:23:29,390 --> 00:23:33,080
I have no skills, but I have strength.

309
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:35,870
I don't think you do.

310
00:23:35,870 --> 00:23:37,950
You see?

311
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:40,420
Follow me, then.

312
00:23:40,420 --> 00:23:42,030
- Me, too? 
 - Yes, help him.

313
00:23:42,030 --> 00:23:43,190
M-Me?

314
00:23:43,190 --> 00:23:46,390
I was going to rest because it's my day off.

315
00:23:47,510 --> 00:23:50,150
- Hand me that. 
 - Okay.

316
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:53,950
What should I start with?

317
00:23:54,590 --> 00:23:56,750
You said you have no skills.

318
00:23:56,750 --> 00:23:58,650
Can you do this stuff?

319
00:23:58,650 --> 00:24:00,890
You just need to change the doorknob.

320
00:24:00,890 --> 00:24:05,060
Of course. I'll try to take care of it myself.

321
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:07,080
Just let me know if you can't.

322
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:09,790
Su Jeong does this with her eyes closed.

323
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:12,910
I'm bad at being bad at things.

324
00:24:18,370 --> 00:24:20,800
Will he do it with bare hands?

325
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:23,340
Go help him.

326
00:24:33,590 --> 00:24:34,610
How do I do this...

327
00:24:34,610 --> 00:24:38,190
You have to glue it if you do it that way.

328
00:24:38,190 --> 00:24:41,320
You do it like this. Got it?

329
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:43,420
And you... No.

330
00:24:43,420 --> 00:24:46,060
Use this to undo this.

331
00:24:46,060 --> 00:24:49,280
I'll try this myself, then.

332
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:51,810
Be careful. Then...

333
00:24:51,810 --> 00:24:53,380
Hold this for me.

334
00:24:53,380 --> 00:24:55,380
- I'll hold it. 
 - Okay.

335
00:24:55,380 --> 00:24:57,190
Is it expensive?

336
00:24:57,190 --> 00:25:00,360
Well, I don't really know.

337
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:01,770
So...

338
00:25:02,580 --> 00:25:04,600
No, no, no.

339
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:06,640
If you don't know how to do this,

340
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:08,280
it'd be good if you let me know.

341
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:10,490
Thank you for teaching me.

342
00:25:11,220 --> 00:25:13,680
- I can do it well. 
 - Can you?

343
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,890
Okay.

344
00:25:21,880 --> 00:25:26,110
Father, I accomplished this important task.

345
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:29,210
You do the same, right?

346
00:25:29,210 --> 00:25:32,180
- The opposite direction. 
 - The same way, right?

347
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:46,320
Why won't he respond?

348
00:25:48,900 --> 00:25:51,710
 Guess what your boyfriend is doing. 

349
00:25:51,710 --> 00:25:53,340
What?

350
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:59,130
There's a lot of concern about

351
00:25:59,130 --> 00:26:00,940
the vacant director position.

352
00:26:00,940 --> 00:26:05,490
Also, about the successor, besides Director Ban—

353
00:26:06,830 --> 00:26:10,780
You think there's no one to replace him?

354
00:26:12,050 --> 00:26:14,440
Call Yongsung Trading's

355
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:16,340
Park Ji Cheol.

356
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:17,740
Yes.

357
00:26:17,740 --> 00:26:20,560
And as for Team Leader Baek Su Jeong—

358
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:22,710
Get rid of her discreetly.

359
00:26:22,710 --> 00:26:24,220
Okay.

360
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:37,350
You worked hard today.

361
00:26:37,350 --> 00:26:39,530
Why don't we have dinner together?

362
00:26:39,530 --> 00:26:42,250
Yes, I'll enjoy it.

363
00:26:42,250 --> 00:26:45,230
How do you know if you'll enjoy it?

364
00:26:45,230 --> 00:26:48,950
What are we supposed to eat today?

365
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:50,240
Should I cook, then?

366
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:53,110
I'm strong,

367
00:26:53,110 --> 00:26:55,350
but I can cook, too.

368
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:58,290
I don't think you can.

369
00:27:15,310 --> 00:27:18,240
He was desperate to impress you all day.

370
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:20,520
That was pretty good, huh?

371
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:24,000
- Impress me? 
 - You're his girlfriend's dad.

372
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:26,920
Right. You don't have to do that.

373
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:29,120
I'm happy as long as Su Jeong is happy.

374
00:27:29,120 --> 00:27:30,360
Hey, come on.

375
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:32,130
I know you didn't trust him.

376
00:27:32,130 --> 00:27:33,330
I didn't?

377
00:27:33,330 --> 00:27:36,190
I didn't? That's not true.

378
00:27:36,190 --> 00:27:38,450
Of course, you're worried.

379
00:27:38,450 --> 00:27:41,740
I don't come from a normal background.

380
00:27:41,740 --> 00:27:45,800
You must trust Su Jeong, but not me.

381
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:47,720
My situation is like this now,

382
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:50,580
but I'll make sure you won't worry.

383
00:27:50,580 --> 00:27:53,230
No matter what,

384
00:27:53,230 --> 00:27:56,190
I won't make her cry or leave her alone.

385
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:01,600
I'm such a bad dad.

386
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:05,200
All I could do was trust her and nothing else.

387
00:28:06,100 --> 00:28:08,340
But I'm relieved, thanks to you.

388
00:28:08,340 --> 00:28:11,610
I'll make sure you won't have to worry.

389
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:22,170
Su Jeong, welcome.

390
00:28:22,170 --> 00:28:23,650
What are you doing?

391
00:28:23,650 --> 00:28:25,200
What's with the headwrap?

392
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:26,790
Welcome, Su Jeong. Let's eat.

393
00:28:26,790 --> 00:28:30,280
My son-in-law is a great cook.

394
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:34,950
- Your what? 
 - I learned how to cook as a child.

395
00:28:34,950 --> 00:28:37,770
The galbijjim is amazing, Brother-in-law.

396
00:28:37,770 --> 00:28:39,100
Brother-in-law?

397
00:28:39,100 --> 00:28:43,200
Su Jeong, I made it because you like that.

398
00:28:45,070 --> 00:28:46,550
All right.

399
00:28:46,550 --> 00:28:48,700
What's all this?

400
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:50,300
Okay.

401
00:28:50,300 --> 00:28:52,480
Wow.

402
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:54,180
Say, "Ah."

403
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,630
What?

404
00:29:02,630 --> 00:29:04,250
Why is it so good?

405
00:29:04,250 --> 00:29:05,930
I know, right?

406
00:29:05,930 --> 00:29:07,400
It's by Chef Ban Ju Yeon.

407
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:09,530
Let's eat.

408
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,730
How nice.

409
00:29:27,730 --> 00:29:32,350
Eating and talking together at home like this.

410
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:39,650
It's my first time since my parents passed away.

411
00:29:40,690 --> 00:29:44,170
He must've had a hard time.

412
00:29:48,370 --> 00:29:50,630
Sleep over.

413
00:29:50,630 --> 00:29:52,220
Pardon?

414
00:29:53,380 --> 00:29:54,900
You worked hard today.

415
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:56,980
Drink with us and sleep over.

416
00:29:56,980 --> 00:29:58,770
We'll have breakfast tomorrow, too.

417
00:29:58,770 --> 00:30:01,600
I'll make breakfast.

418
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:04,110
- Would that be okay? 
 - Of course.

419
00:30:04,110 --> 00:30:05,500
Let's share my room.

420
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:07,180
Your room is messy.

421
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:08,960
An important guest can't sleep there.

422
00:30:08,960 --> 00:30:10,980
Sleep with me in the main bedroom.

423
00:30:10,980 --> 00:30:13,500
You'll snore up a storm.

424
00:30:13,500 --> 00:30:15,750
He can't sleep. You'll sleep in my room, right?

425
00:30:15,750 --> 00:30:17,740
You both want me. This is tricky.

426
00:30:17,740 --> 00:30:20,160
I only have one body.

427
00:30:20,750 --> 00:30:22,310
Just sleep in my room.

428
00:30:22,310 --> 00:30:24,010
- Are you crazy? 
 - Are you crazy?

429
00:30:24,010 --> 00:30:25,830
What are you thinking?

430
00:30:25,830 --> 00:30:28,490
I can sleep in the living room.

431
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:31,650
Oh, okay.

432
00:31:19,110 --> 00:31:21,410
(Goodnight.)

433
00:32:16,110 --> 00:32:17,530
 Are you sleeping? 

434
00:32:17,530 --> 00:32:20,670
 Can I see you briefly if you aren't? 

435
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:29,350
What is it?

436
00:32:39,430 --> 00:32:41,730
I bought this for you,

437
00:32:41,730 --> 00:32:44,300
but I realized I only got one.

438
00:32:44,300 --> 00:32:45,570
Dad or Su Bin

439
00:32:45,570 --> 00:32:47,100
would drink it if I put it in the fridge.

440
00:32:47,100 --> 00:32:49,050
I thought you were a filial daughter.

441
00:32:49,050 --> 00:32:51,390
You only care about me.

442
00:32:52,190 --> 00:32:56,140
Thank you. I was craving something sweet.

443
00:32:56,140 --> 00:32:58,730
Are you okay after drinking?

444
00:32:58,730 --> 00:32:59,950
I'm fine.

445
00:32:59,950 --> 00:33:04,380
You're the only one who could kill me.

446
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:09,280
Anyway, what did you do today?

447
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,000
I told you to read comic books and rest.

448
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:14,800
I had tteokbokki with your brother and helped Father.

449
00:33:15,990 --> 00:33:17,440
You know what?

450
00:33:17,440 --> 00:33:20,410
I'm a man who knows how to change doorknobs.

451
00:33:21,230 --> 00:33:23,910
Amazing. You did that?

452
00:33:23,910 --> 00:33:27,150
You're a good cook, too. You're good at everything.

453
00:33:27,150 --> 00:33:29,280
I know.

454
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:31,710
I know how to do something.

455
00:33:33,020 --> 00:33:35,180
Good work.

456
00:33:36,320 --> 00:33:39,300
Was everything okay with you?

457
00:33:39,300 --> 00:33:42,890
Yes, of course, everything was fine.

458
00:33:42,890 --> 00:33:44,890
That's good to hear.

459
00:33:44,890 --> 00:33:46,500
Read comic books since you're here.

460
00:33:46,500 --> 00:33:49,010
Should I? Let's read together.

461
00:33:49,010 --> 00:33:50,410
I'll recommend you one.

462
00:33:50,410 --> 00:33:52,150
Sounds good.

463
00:33:55,250 --> 00:33:56,340
This is it.

464
00:33:56,340 --> 00:34:01,700
I read it when I feel combative.

465
00:34:01,700 --> 00:34:04,080
- Did you get that autograph? 
 - Yes, right.

466
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:09,200
You can say this is one of my proud achievements.

467
00:34:13,240 --> 00:34:15,330
This is what happened...

468
00:34:16,450 --> 00:34:19,240
Look where I marked it.

469
00:34:28,620 --> 00:34:31,500
You don't have to see me off.

470
00:34:31,500 --> 00:34:34,500
I wish I could drive you to work.

471
00:34:34,500 --> 00:34:37,770
But the breakfast with family is more important.

472
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:40,700
Did you sleep comfortably?

473
00:34:40,700 --> 00:34:42,400
You should've slept comfortably at home.

474
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:44,850
Dad and Su Bin took it too far.

475
00:34:44,850 --> 00:34:46,150
I felt comfortable.

476
00:34:46,150 --> 00:34:48,220
More than I do at home.

477
00:34:49,530 --> 00:34:51,860
That's a relief, then.

478
00:34:51,860 --> 00:34:55,740
I'm glad you're a loved daughter and sister.

479
00:34:55,740 --> 00:34:58,230
I can be loved because of that, too.

480
00:34:58,230 --> 00:35:00,240
Like family.

481
00:35:02,890 --> 00:35:04,110
Go inside now.

482
00:35:04,110 --> 00:35:06,420
You'll be late for breakfast.

483
00:35:09,670 --> 00:35:11,310
I'll go.

484
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:15,790
Su Jeong.

485
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,760
I made up my mind yesterday.

486
00:35:24,460 --> 00:35:28,760
I won't make you cry for the third time.

487
00:35:37,390 --> 00:35:39,890
So, get back safely.

488
00:35:39,890 --> 00:35:42,940
Don't fall or get hurt.

489
00:35:42,940 --> 00:35:45,520
Don't worry about me, either.

490
00:36:11,020 --> 00:36:13,050
   

491
00:36:22,300 --> 00:36:24,380
   

492
00:36:27,890 --> 00:36:29,840
What's this, Team Leader?

493
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:31,260
Why would you...

494
00:36:31,260 --> 00:36:33,140
This makes no sense.

495
00:36:33,140 --> 00:36:36,590
They can't do this over a false rumor.

496
00:36:36,590 --> 00:36:40,220
The rumor is true.

497
00:36:40,220 --> 00:36:41,330
Pardon?

498
00:36:41,330 --> 00:36:43,110
You said it wasn't then.

499
00:36:43,110 --> 00:36:45,170
With Director?

500
00:36:45,170 --> 00:36:48,230
I'm sorry. It wasn't true then.

501
00:36:48,230 --> 00:36:51,250
But we are dating now.

502
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:54,320
Okay.

503
00:36:54,320 --> 00:36:56,070
Okay, but still—

504
00:36:56,070 --> 00:36:58,310
Yes, it's unjust.

505
00:36:58,310 --> 00:37:01,720
Team Leader, you won't just let this slide.

506
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:03,530
Right?

507
00:37:09,460 --> 00:37:13,740
I'm sorry this happened while we are busy.

508
00:37:21,070 --> 00:37:23,090
Team Leader.

509
00:37:28,770 --> 00:37:30,550
Why did she send her

510
00:37:30,550 --> 00:37:32,430
grandson's rumored girlfriend here?

511
00:37:32,430 --> 00:37:34,370
She probably has no skills.

512
00:37:34,370 --> 00:37:35,910
That's why she sent her here.

513
00:37:35,910 --> 00:37:39,130
So, she'd do nothing, give up on her own, and leave.

514
00:37:39,130 --> 00:37:41,010
Excuse me.

515
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:44,720
I won't get in your way.

516
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:46,840
If you have any task that's a hassle for you,

517
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:48,990
just give it to me.

518
00:37:48,990 --> 00:37:52,070
I'm sure there are things I can do.

519
00:37:57,300 --> 00:38:00,140
W-What? Huh?

520
00:38:00,140 --> 00:38:04,060
Something must be broken. It won't shut off.

521
00:38:04,060 --> 00:38:06,230
What? An hour?

522
00:38:06,230 --> 00:38:07,870
H-Hey...

523
00:38:08,570 --> 00:38:10,510
Let me give it a try.

524
00:38:11,140 --> 00:38:13,680
This isn't something anyone can fix.

525
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:15,970
I have electrician and fire inspection certificates.

526
00:38:15,970 --> 00:38:17,800
You don't mind, right?

527
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:43,710
It worked.

528
00:38:49,110 --> 00:38:51,330
What else can I do?

529
00:38:56,180 --> 00:38:58,190
Just one moment.

530
00:39:01,460 --> 00:39:04,820
Why are you all standing here...

531
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:18,830
What are you doing?

532
00:39:18,830 --> 00:39:21,340
I thought you didn't tolerate stuff like this.

533
00:39:21,340 --> 00:39:23,790
How about you? Why are you angry?

534
00:39:23,790 --> 00:39:25,160
I thought you'd be happy to

535
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:27,710
not see the annoying junior in meetings.

536
00:39:27,710 --> 00:39:30,140
The reason I don't like you is because

537
00:39:30,140 --> 00:39:32,400
you don't tolerate anything.

538
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:34,400
I've walked around eggshells and

539
00:39:34,400 --> 00:39:37,400
gave up on self-respect to come this far.

540
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:39,410
But you never tolerate anything.

541
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:40,770
You say everything you want to say

542
00:39:40,770 --> 00:39:43,450
and protect your sense of pride.

543
00:39:43,450 --> 00:39:45,410
You think you're so superior.

544
00:39:45,410 --> 00:39:48,480
I really hated that, but...

545
00:39:49,950 --> 00:39:52,230
But seeing you tolerate this—

546
00:39:52,230 --> 00:39:53,950
You hate this, too?

547
00:39:53,950 --> 00:39:55,650
Yes.

548
00:39:55,650 --> 00:39:57,440
I hate it.

549
00:39:57,440 --> 00:39:59,300
Baek Su Jeong,

550
00:39:59,300 --> 00:40:01,910
- why don't you just— 
 - Senior,

551
00:40:01,910 --> 00:40:04,610
I haven't tolerated things all this time...

552
00:40:04,610 --> 00:40:07,110
to protect myself.

553
00:40:07,110 --> 00:40:09,760
But to protect someone else,

554
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:12,040
I do have to tolerate some things.

555
00:40:13,170 --> 00:40:15,290
I'll get going now.

556
00:40:50,010 --> 00:40:52,120
- Hello. 
 - Hello.

557
00:40:57,340 --> 00:40:58,770
Please drink this.

558
00:40:58,770 --> 00:41:00,780
- Thank you. 
 - Thank you.

559
00:41:00,780 --> 00:41:02,810
Thank you.

560
00:41:02,810 --> 00:41:05,130
That's the new director.

561
